    {
      "question": "A rectangle has a length $x$ and a width $x-3$. If the area of this rectangle is numerically equal to the perimeter of a square with side $x$, find the quadratic equation representing this condition.",
      "answer": "$x^2 - 7x = 0$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "The area of the rectangle is given by $Length \\times Width = x(x-3) = x^2 - 3x$.",
          "The perimeter of a square with side $x$ is $4 \\times side = 4x$.",
          "Equate the two expressions: $x^2 - 3x = 4x$.",
          "Rearrange the terms into standard form $ax^2 + bx + c = 0$: $x^2 - 3x - 4x = 0 \\Rightarrow x^2 - 7x = 0$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$Area = x(x-3) \\\\ Perimeter = 4x \\\\ x(x-3) = 4x \\\\ x^2 - 3x = 4x \\\\ x^2 - 3x - 4x = 0 \\\\ x^2 - 7x = 0$"
      },
      "topic": "Quadratic Equations",
      "subtopic": "Formation of quadratic equations",
